top.item: Jewish Community Center Of Staten Island
Seventh Avenue Center For Family Services

cachedContents.largest: Note: Students who qualify for Free and Reduced Lunch have priority after siblings.

top.item: Alert: Program may have income or other eligibility requirements. Contact for more information.
Note: Students who qualify for Free and Reduced Lunch and/or are English Language Learners will have priority for 45% of seats.
Note: Program manages own admissions. Contact directly to apply.
Note: Program prioritizes students in Districts 5 and 6.
Note: Program prioritizes students zoned to 08X014, 08X071, or 08X072.

Note: Students from families impacted by incarceration will have priority for 10% of seats and students who qualify for Free and Reduced Lunch will have priority for 60% of seats. Families impacted by incarceration should contact the school directly.

Note: Students in District 15 are prioritized for two-thirds of seats and students in District 13 are prioritized for the remaining third. Within each district group, students who qualify for Free and Reduced Lunch and/or are English Language Learners will have priority for 35% of those seats.

Note: Students who are English Language Learners and/or are in the child welfare system will have priority for 20% of seats. If the applicant is in the child welfare system please contact the school directly.
Note: Students who qualify for Free and Reduced Lunch have priority after siblings.
Note: Prioritizes Coast Guard families stationed at Fort Wadsworth.
